insert into reviews (id, comments, headline, rating, review_time, customer_id, product_id, votes) values (21, 'I am pleased with this purchase. The charging cords appear sturdy. Feel sturdy. I had no problems with charging my phone. The red color cords was a plus.', 'Sturdy charger', 5, TIMESTAMP '2021-02-06 11:33:45.810000', 25, 45, 2);
insert into reviews (id, comments, headline, rating, review_time, customer_id, product_id, votes) values (22, 'I liked these chargers and they were pretty cheap, but you get what you pay for I guess. No visible damage or anything, just noticed at some point when the phone was on the charger it wasn''t charging.', 'Chargers Randomly Stopped Working One by One', 3, TIMESTAMP '2021-10-19 11:33:45.810000', 33, 45, 2);
insert into reviews (id, comments, headline, rating, review_time, customer_id, product_id, votes) values (24, 'Seems to actually work more reliably than it''s faster brother (WH16NS40). I''ve always had some issues watching some Blu-rays (stuttering, visual artifacts, etc..) with that other drive. The (WH14NS40) do not exhibit these same issues and burns DVDs just as fast. ', 'Works as expected', 4, TIMESTAMP '2021-11-16 16:47:08.983000', 5, 91, 0);
insert into reviews (id, comments, headline, rating, review_time, customer_id, product_id, votes) values (25, 'Best camera on the market right now', 'Best camera on the market right now', 5, TIMESTAMP '2021-11-16 16:50:19.416000', 7, 11, 2);
insert into reviews (id, comments, headline, rating, review_time, customer_id, product_id, votes) values (26, 'I chose this product because the description said it was a 7200 RPM drive. As you can see by the picture I have uploaded it is only a 5400 RPM drive. I would have gone with another brand had I known this. ', 'Not 7200 RPM', 4, TIMESTAMP '2021-01-21 12:09:43.511000', 4, 88, 0);
insert into reviews (id, comments, headline, rating, review_time, customer_id, product_id, votes) values (27, 'he M50 is probably better classed as a high end point-and-shoot and while it has come nice features, it should not be used to replace a DSLR. In my case, I had to sell my 6D because of the pandemic work situation and this has been a sobering step downward. ', 'Nice Camera but NOT a DSLR', 4, TIMESTAMP '2021-11-12 12:16:04.723000', 4, 1, -2);
insert into reviews (id, comments, headline, rating, review_time, customer_id, product_id, votes) values (28, 'I got this card for my galaxy S9. It had a very good chip installed in it before (Samsung 256G Evo Select) which I liked. But I wanted to max out my S9 both in its 400G max capacity and in the speed to record. This chip/card does record 1080p 60fps with no problems at all. ', 'Worked perfect in my Galaxy S9 plus and now my LG Wing.', 5, TIMESTAMP '2021-11-03 12:17:55.769000', 4, 50, 0);
insert into reviews (id, comments, headline, rating, review_time, customer_id, product_id, votes) values (29, 'Loaded with 64GB of RAM and a 1TB M2 SSD, running esxi. I LOVE it. Great small form factor, doesn''t use much energy, and whisper quiet. This is replacing and old Dell R710 which is the exact opposite; loud, hot, and power hungry.', 'Fantastic Device', 5, TIMESTAMP '2021-11-10 13:09:26.252000', 4, 64, 0);
insert into reviews (id, comments, headline, rating, review_time, customer_id, product_id, votes) values (30, 'I buy a lot of Samsung EVO MicroSD Cards of various sizes (32GB, 64GB, 128GB, etc.) & haven''t had any issues yet. I use them in phones, Raspberry PI projects, cameras, Nintendo Switch, chromebooks, etc.', 'Good MicroSD Card, Sometimes Bad SD Adapter', 4, TIMESTAMP '2021-11-07 13:14:07.275000', 11, 49, 0);
insert into reviews (id, comments, headline, rating, review_time, customer_id, product_id, votes) values (31, 'This is my 3rd S6 edge through warranty. My 1st one the front glass cracked for no reason at all. My second edge battery malfunctioned. The one I currently have has a crack across the top right I have never dropped the phone or applied pressure to it in my opinion the phone front glass is no good. ', 'The front glass is terrible', 3, TIMESTAMP '2021-11-15 13:16:28.228000', 11, 28, 0);
insert into reviews (id, comments, headline, rating, review_time, customer_id, product_id, votes) values (32, 'Everything is good but not suiting my requirement as i have a vision issue. Please help me with the returning of this model with another model as an exceptional case', 'Not matching my requirement', 4, TIMESTAMP '2021-10-21 13:21:47.436000', 11, 76, 0);
insert into reviews (id, comments, headline, rating, review_time, customer_id, product_id, votes) values (33, 'First off the customer service is dismissive and unhelpful. Secondly, I bought two packages of these as I have four slots...like most all computers built. They are not compatible if you have four of them so essentially you will make the other slots inactive by using these.', 'Incompatible with itself', 2, TIMESTAMP '2021-10-26 13:25:32.660000', 11, 99, 1);
insert into reviews (id, comments, headline, rating, review_time, customer_id, product_id, votes) values (34, 'This is one very shiny toy. It took a while for me to post this review because at first I was not sure if maybe it had a focus problem. After three weeks it is clear that it is operator error and learning curve. I will post some sample pics.', 'This is one VERY shiny object. :)', 5, TIMESTAMP '2021-10-29 13:36:23.869000', 17, 22, 0);
insert into reviews (id, comments, headline, rating, review_time, customer_id, product_id, votes) values (35, 'Wow! It took me no time to install this thing and it has made my 5 year old laptop like new again! I replaced the laptop battery too, but I think it wasn''t necessary.  ', 'Quick install and great speed', 5, TIMESTAMP '2021-11-02 13:40:14.821000', 17, 95, 0);
insert into reviews (id, comments, headline, rating, review_time, customer_id, product_id, votes) values (36, 'Drive works and performs as intended. This is my first Blu-Ray drive, so I have no comparison to note performance.', 'Works well (with a noted installation issue)', 4, TIMESTAMP '2021-11-21 13:41:56.036000', 17, 90, 0);
insert into reviews (id, comments, headline, rating, review_time, customer_id, product_id, votes) values (37, 'I like almost everything about this camera. If it had an articulating screen for selfies or vloging it would be perfect. I wish they kept the photo timelapse feature.', 'Almost perfect', 4, TIMESTAMP '2021-11-21 16:13:12.348000', 10, 11, 1);
insert into reviews (id, comments, headline, rating, review_time, customer_id, product_id, votes) values (38, 'Windows 10 automatically detected the cards and ran it, which is nice. It, however, kept dropping my 5G connection. The 2.4G connection was constant. After installing the drivers from the CD included, the card became more stable. ', 'Make sure you use the TP-Link Drivers', 5, TIMESTAMP '2021-11-21 16:22:24.835000', 8, 106, 0);
insert into reviews (id, comments, headline, rating, review_time, customer_id, product_id, votes) values (39, 'I got this on sale. I''m glad I did. It''s already good RAM at it''s base speed, and it''s fantastic when you overclock it.', 'Some of the fastest RAM for the price', 5, TIMESTAMP '2021-11-21 16:24:37.860000', 8, 99, -1);
insert into reviews (id, comments, headline, rating, review_time, customer_id, product_id, votes) values (40, 'This is my 3rd Legion 5 laptop. I got the 1st one from Walmart with the following specs: 4600H Ryzen 5, 120HZ 250 nits screen, 256 GB SSD + 1TB HDD, and only a GTX 1650ti. My 2nd was the same but a slightly cheaper price when it was on sale from Lenovo which featured the same screen...', 'Great Value with a few Caveats', 4, TIMESTAMP '2021-11-21 16:35:14.396000', 8, 71, 0);
insert into reviews (id, comments, headline, rating, review_time, customer_id, product_id, votes) values (41, 'Perfect $250 phone', 'Perfect $250 phone', 5, TIMESTAMP '2021-11-21 16:54:14.406000', 8, 29, 0);
insert into reviews (id, comments, headline, rating, review_time, customer_id, product_id, votes) values (42, 'Since this is a Microsoft product, it was extremely easy to set up. With my previous computer, I had to work on two computers for about a month, before I could switch. With the Surface, it took just a few minutes! It’s fast, slick, light weight and I love it!', 'Fast, slick and so easy to set up', 5, TIMESTAMP '2021-11-21 16:58:13.141000', 28, 76, 0);
insert into reviews (id, comments, headline, rating, review_time, customer_id, product_id, votes) values (43, 'Let''s get this out of the way first: this is, first and foremost, an entry level mirrorless camera. It won''t have the most functions or the highest image/build quality of the best lens out of the box, but that''s not what I was expecting when I ordered this awesome camera.', 'Ideal for what I need it for!', 4, TIMESTAMP '2021-11-21 17:01:47.438000', 28, 1, 2);
insert into reviews (id, comments, headline, rating, review_time, customer_id, product_id, votes) values (44, 'Product information says that batteries included (2). No battery is there. Moreover it needs 4 batteries', 'Not satisfied', 3, TIMESTAMP '2021-11-21 17:10:48.759000', 28, 16, 0);
insert into reviews (id, comments, headline, rating, review_time, customer_id, product_id, votes) values (45, 'I had a heck of a time getting my laser to line up with this tripod. It was not very smooth when trying to adjust a minute amount - I tried all the adjustment screws to no avail. Too much this way...oops, too much the other. ', 'Ok, but very hard to adjust', 3, TIMESTAMP '2021-11-21 17:14:01.116000', 28, 23, 1);
insert into reviews (id, comments, headline, rating, review_time, customer_id, product_id, votes) values (46, 'I have a nearly 9 year old CyberPower desktop with an Asus P6T Motherboard and wanted to eliminate a potential point of failure to eek out a little more longevity. And if I got some enhanced performance, all the better. Turns out it was a very good move.', 'Quick and hassle free migration from HDD to Samsung EVO 860 SSD on aging desktop', 5, TIMESTAMP '2021-11-21 17:18:40.424000', 28, 8, 0);
insert into reviews (id, comments, headline, rating, review_time, customer_id, product_id, votes) values (47, 'My first impression is that the board is very stable, haven''t had any random blue-screens. It all seems to work fine, as long as you''re not really a super-power-user. The board does need a few pre-OS install tweaks to really be good, and there''s a few things not to do with this board. ', 'Stable board, but needs a few pre-install tweaks', 4, TIMESTAMP '2021-11-21 17:19:49.096000', 28, 103, 0);
insert into reviews (id, comments, headline, rating, review_time, customer_id, product_id, votes) values (48, 'The card is playing everything no problem and very quiet. The fans do not spin at all unless you are over 60 degree celsius so don''t panic it is not a defective card it just has a 0 db mode for noise. ', 'Card is awesome and don''t panic', 5, TIMESTAMP '2021-11-21 17:24:43.367000', 32, 84, 0);
insert into reviews (id, comments, headline, rating, review_time, customer_id, product_id, votes) values (49, 'Just like some of the 1 and 2 star reviews states, you do get BDOS, but! with windows 10, if you let it restart itself after the bdos, it will run a diagnostic mode. Let it run and fix itself and it will boot up correctly. ', '!! Before You Buy It, Expect This !!', 4, TIMESTAMP '2021-11-21 17:26:12.361000', 32, 105, 0);
insert into reviews (id, comments, headline, rating, review_time, customer_id, product_id, votes) values (50, 'I was initially very satisfied with the purchase. The machine is great looking and the screen is very nice. It was the perfect balance of price and capability for my needs.', 'Worked Great Until Windows updated', 3, TIMESTAMP '2021-11-21 17:31:45.528000', 32, 66, 1);
insert into reviews (id, comments, headline, rating, review_time, customer_id, product_id, votes) values (51, 'I just installed this in my mid-2012 MacBook Pro over the weekend. We use the 850 version in all our desktops at work for the last 3 years and they have been solid. The only drawback is the lack of software for Mac. ', 'Great Product Overall', 4, TIMESTAMP '2021-11-21 17:34:07.928000', 32, 8, 0);
insert into reviews (id, comments, headline, rating, review_time, customer_id, product_id, votes) values (52, 'I ordered this because I know from experience that Kingston Hyperx Fury is some of the best ram out there. Way better than Corsair, don''t let anyone tell you different. I still have my ddr3 Hyperx ram in my old pc and it''s been going strong for over 10 years!', 'Hyperx Fury is the best ram you can buy.', 5, TIMESTAMP '2021-11-21 17:37:01.782000', 32, 101, 0);
insert into reviews (id, comments, headline, rating, review_time, customer_id, product_id, votes) values (53, 'Despite the ads on the product page this motherboard DOES NOT have a BIOS QFlash button, which you need to update the BIOS to become compatible with the new ryzen 7 5800X series. ', 'Not out-of-box compatible with Ryzen 7 5800x', 3, TIMESTAMP '2021-11-21 17:38:10.551000', 32, 102, 0);
insert into reviews (id, comments, headline, rating, review_time, customer_id, product_id, votes) values (54, 'There are a few annoyances with this product those being lack of thunderbolt 3, limited screen real estate coupled with big bezels and the biggest gripe of all being poor battery life compared to the competition (Hp, Dell and Lenovo).', 'A few gripes but overall a good product.', 4, TIMESTAMP '2021-11-21 17:50:08.457000', 34, 76, 0);
insert into reviews (id, comments, headline, rating, review_time, customer_id, product_id, votes) values (55, 'I bought this camera because I wanted more performance than my iPhone without dropping a ton of money into a heavy camera that wouldn’t be practical for carrying on hikes.', 'Great camera for a great price.', 5, TIMESTAMP '2021-11-21 17:53:25.012000', 34, 3, 0);
insert into reviews (id, comments, headline, rating, review_time, customer_id, product_id, votes) values (56, 'I am not a phone gamer. I didn''t buy this card to get gaming speed, but to store the huge files that result from 4K or 8K recordings, to take movies with me on the road, store tons of pictures and most importantly offload my Android apps from internal storage.', 'Enormous capacity but Android has trouble keeping apps in the card', 4, TIMESTAMP '2021-11-21 17:55:46.552000', 34, 50, 0);
insert into reviews (id, comments, headline, rating, review_time, customer_id, product_id, votes) values (57, 'This was exactly what I was looking for, very light and compact for travel and very sturdy. I used it last at the Delicate Arch during sunset on an uneven “bowl” surface and I was able to adjust the legs. It held up my 5D Mark IV with 16-35 f/4L or 24-105L attached very well. ', 'Compact, sturdy, functional', 5, TIMESTAMP '2021-11-21 17:57:28.288000', 34, 24, 0);
